Project ideas
=============



Vaccination at schools
----------------------
Question to answer:
- Which schools are safe for a child who cannot be vaccinated for a certain disease?

Data wish list:
- School vaccination rates for different communicatable diseases
- herd immunity treshold for different diseases


Sources: 
- Herd immunity threshold data:
http://www.bt.cdc.gov/agent/smallpox/training/overview/pdf/eradicationhistory.pdf
- list of reported diseases:
https://www.cdph.ca.gov/pubsforms/forms/CtrldForms/cdph286.pdf
http://ochealthinfo.com/civicax/filebank/blobdload.aspx?BlobID=13145
- California school immunatization data:
http://www.cdph.ca.gov/programs/immunize/pages/immunizationlevels.aspx
- Vermont school immunization data:
http://www.healthvermont.gov/hc/imm/ImmSurv.aspx
- coverage rates:
http://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/imz-managers/coverage/index.html


! Similar project:
http://spreadsheets.latimes.com/immunization-levels-california/






Heatlh effect of airports
-------------------------
Question to answer:
- Do people near airports are more exposed to certain medical conditions? 
- Do they need to take certain drugs more prevalently?


Data wish list:
- drug prescriptions by area
- drug perscription by income brackets
- income bracket by area
(- mortality rate by area)

Data:
- mortality:
http://ahrf.hrsa.gov/categories.htm#3
- drug prescription
http://www.cms.gov/Research-Statistics-Data-and-Systems/Statistics-Trends-and-Reports/Medicare-Provider-Charge-Data/index.html
- income vs residential area
http://www.irs.gov/uac/SOI-Tax-Stats-Individual-Income-Tax-Statistics-ZIP-Code-Data-%28SOI%29


